div.div: Impromptu for the Next Prime Minister

@battis I actually ended up making a fork of this project, though it uses common js since I depend on common.js modules for my Typescript projects. if you'd like I can make a PR that adds typing and fixes the file problem. It turns out the file problem stems from url.resolve() with Windows paths. Because windows use \ in its system paths, we end up with paths like "file://C:\path\to\file". I converted all / in my file URLs to \ and it seemed to work. It probably has something to do with how url.resolve work, though I'm not too familiar with that myself.
